# API & Dependencies Rules

## OpenAI API
- Use OpenAI Vision API for image analysis
- Include proper error handling and timeout handling
- Store API keys in environment variables
- Implement retry logic for transient failures

## Dependencies
- Keep minimal and well-documented
- Use official OpenAI Node.js SDK
- Include dotenv, Winston, Handlebars, Express
- Add dependencies only when necessary

## Current Stack
- `axios` - HTTP client
- `dotenv` - Environment variables
- `exif-parser` - EXIF data extraction
- `express` - Web framework
- `express-handlebars` - Templates
- `multer` - File uploads
- `openai` - AI API client
- `winston` - Logging

```javascript
// Good: API with error handling
const getAIInsights = async (imageId) => {
  try {
    const response = await axios.request(apiConfig);
    logInfo('AI analysis completed', imageId);
    return response.data;
  } catch (error) {
    logError('AI analysis failed', error);
    throw new Error('AI Processing Failed');
  }
};
